"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90949","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-10","<p>On 31 March 2010, there were 38,000 full time equivalent Civil Servants employed in the Yorkshire and the Humber region. The latest available statistics for 2013 show that this number reduced to 31,590 as at 31 March 2013.</p><p>To help deal with the deficit which this Government inherited in 2010, the Government has reduced the size of the Civil Service by 17% since the 2010 General Election. It is now at its smallest since the Second World War, representing a significant increase in efficiency and productivity. This reduction helped save taxpayers £2.4bn last year alone, against a 2009/10 baseline.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-09-10T15:54:59.132401Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90949/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90949/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-04","Civil Servants: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many full-time equivalent jobs with the Civil Service or government agencies there were in Yorkshire in May 2010; and how many such jobs there are now.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","905301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91337","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-10","<p>We are working to offer practical support to the youth sector at a time when local authorities continue to make difficult decisions on how to deliver services. This support focuses on promoting delivery models for innovative services, including mutuals, and better measurement of the impact of youth services on the lives of young people.</p><p> </p>","Braintree","Mr Brooks Newmark",,"2014-09-10T15:47:48.9253405Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91337/answer","Biography information for Mr Brooks Newmark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91337/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-04","Youth Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to maintain the level of youth services provision.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","905304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91338","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-10","<p>Social action, including volunteering, is changing lives. This Government – through the Centre for Social Action – is proud to be supporting projects that put social action into practice.</p><p>Cabinet Office and Nesta recently hosted the ‘People Helping People’ conference to promote the important opportunities social action presents.</p><p> </p>","Braintree","Mr Brooks Newmark",,"2014-09-10T15:52:00.8989281Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91338/answer","Biography information for Mr Brooks Newmark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91338/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-04","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent steps the Government has taken to promote social action and volunteering.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","905306"
