"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90280","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-05","<p>Estimates of the volume losses associated with the illicit market for cigarettes for the period 2008-09 to 2012-13 are published in ‘Tobacco Tax Gap estimates: 2012-13’. The figures are available in table 1.1.</p><p> </p><p>These estimates cannot be disaggregated by the type of illicit activity, e.g. through smuggling, counterfeiting or other fraud, or by any geographical level lower than the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The methodology for producing the estimates are provided in the ‘Methodological Annex for Measuring Tax Gaps 2013’.</p><p> </p><p>The ‘Tobacco Tax Gap estimates” can be accessed via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/249543/131009_Publication_of_Tobacco_Tax_Gap_estimates_2012-13.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/249543/131009_Publication_of_Tobacco_Tax_Gap_estimates_2012-13.pdf</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-09-05T13:05:50.29224Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90280/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90280/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Tobacco: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of cigarettes on which tax has not been paid in (a) Gillingham and Rainham constituency, (b) Kent and (c) England in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","207961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90281","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-05","<p>Details of the eligibility criteria for Tax-Free Childcare can be found in Chapter 2 of <em>Delivering Tax-Free Childcare: the Government’s response to the consultation on design and operation</em>: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/318953/PU1607_Tax_free_Childcare_response.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/318953/PU1607_Tax_free_Childcare_response.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-09-05T12:58:06.7770763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90281/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90281/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether households comprising (a) one disabled parent unable to work and another parent in work and (b) a single disabled parent will be entitled to receive help through tax free childcare.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","207930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90282","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-09","<p>No estimate has been made. Data is not available on the VAT paid on repairs and maintenance to protected buildings as this is not itemised separately on VAT returns.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-09-09T14:38:44.2472761Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90282/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90282/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Listed Buildings: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the money accrued to the public purse through VAT paid on the repair and maintenance of protected buildings.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","207896"
