"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90284","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-09","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) is active in assessing and tackling the risks of evasion, avoidance and error amongst large businesses. HMRC's Large Business directorate supports work to tackle fraud within supply chains, as well as monitoring the behaviour of large businesses themselves.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Precise numbers giving the information in the form requested is not centrally held and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-09-09T14:49:49.4908808Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90284/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90284/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Business: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many HM Revenue and Customs tax reviews of large companies have revealed instances of significant evasion in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","207833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90285","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-09","<p>Oil companies account for the repayment of duty on petrol subject to the vapour recovery process in their monthly duty return, so there is no disbursement by HMRC to these companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Eligibility for the Excise Payment Security System does not apply to or exclude particular sectors; criteria are published by HMRC, and apply to all applicants. I can confirm that EPSS approval has been granted to petrol retailers in 2014.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","207842 ; 207843","2014-09-09T14:52:53.9058783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90285/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90285/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Fuels: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Excise Payment Security System has been approved for use by individual retail petrol filling stations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Hart","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart","207850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90286","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-09","<p>Oil companies account for the repayment of duty on petrol subject to the vapour recovery process in their monthly duty return, so there is no disbursement by HMRC to these companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Eligibility for the Excise Payment Security System does not apply to or exclude particular sectors; criteria are published by HMRC, and apply to all applicants. I can confirm that EPSS approval has been granted to petrol retailers in 2014.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","207843 ; 207850","2014-09-09T14:52:53.343348Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90286/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90286/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-02","Oil: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has been disbursed to oil supply companies for the repayment of duty on petrol subject to vapour recovery since January 2013.","false","Biography information for Simon Hart","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart","207842"
