"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90364","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-13","<p /> <p>Recovering overpaid benefit is a high priority for DWP and we take all reasonable and lawful steps to achieve this. We are unable to supply the information requested because of our duties under data protection legislation.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-13T09:14:53.7907669Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90364/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90364/answer","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90364/answer/previousversion/18502","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-02","Social Security Benefits: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much money fraudulently claimed by Ms Janet Curtis has been recovered.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","207901"
