"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90006","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-08","<p>There are no plans to recommend to Her Majesty The Queen that any change should be made to the UK National Anthem, nor are there any plans to introduce an official English Anthem.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-08T13:12:23.2106513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90006/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90006/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-01","National Anthems","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will bring forward proposals for an English national anthem.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","207647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90007","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-04","<p>The Government is investing up to £150m in the SuperConnected Cities Programme to support UK cities to develop the digital infrastructure capability required to remain internationally competitive.</p><p>In addition there has also been a substantial increase in planned commercial infrastructure investment in urban areas including, BT committing an additional £50million to their commercial roll-out; Virgin Media investing to improve its superfast footprint by 100,000 premises and a range of other providers making investments in cities such as York, Coventry and Peterborough. These investments will benefit both businesses and domestic households. There is also the ongoing roll-out of 4G which will make a significant impact on connectivity in urban locations.</p><p>The Government is also working to drive down costs of network delivery and has amended the planning regulations and Electronic Communications code supported the European Directive on measures to reduce broadband deployment costs and has a universal basic broadband commitment to ensure minimum service levels.</p><p>When Government reviews outstanding coverage issues in urban locations after the closure of the SME voucher initiative in March 2015 we will be better placed to identify the most challenging areas and to consider the most appropriate and effective method of intervention at that time.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-04T14:12:41.1408206Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90007/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90007/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-01","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps can be taken to provide broadband services to residential properties in major cities where (a) commercial internet providers have deemed the street cabinets serving that commercially unviable and (b) the local authority is restricted in its ability to use public funds to build broadband networks in contravention of state aid regulations.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","207611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90008","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>Storm Shadow continues to provide the UK with a unique capability for precision strike against high value hardened targets without exposing aircraft and crews to higher than necessary levels of risk.<br><br>The Storm Shadow Mid Life Refurbishment concept phase is considering options to maintain the Storm Shadow Weapons System Capability in order to meet our planning requirements. We have agreed to exchange information with France on our respective national refurbishment and upgrade programmes for Storm Shadow/SCALP EG (the French name for Storm Shadow), underpinned by a Memorandum of Understanding that was signed at the Farnborough International Air Show in July 2014.<br><br>I announced in July that the Storm Shadow is to be integrated onto the RAF's Typhoon aircraft to enter service in 2018.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-08T15:26:35.6194928Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90008/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90008/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on development of the Storm Shadow stand-off weapon; what assessment he has made of its potential advantages to the UK's defence capabilities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90009","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answers I gave on 17 July 2014 (Official Report, column 797W) to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson) and 1 September 2014 (Official Report, column 95W) to the hon. Member for North Durham (Mr Jones).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-08T15:15:40.1778046Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90009/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90009/answer","20140717 - Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft[1].doc ; 20140901 - Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft[1].doc","20140717 - Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft[1].doc ; 20140901 - Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft[1].doc","20130717 Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft ; 20140901 Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft","20130717 Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft ; 20140901 Hansard extract European Fighter Aircraft","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90009/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on development of the Active Electronically Scanned Array (AESA) Captor-E radar; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90010","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>The MBDA Brimstone 2 will enhance the multi-role capability of the Typhoon aircraft as it is effective against challenging, high speed and manoeuvring targets over land and sea.<br><br>Work is underway to evaluate the integration of Brimstone 2 with the Typhoon aircraft. On 2 June 2014, BAE Systems was awarded a contract worth in the region of £5 million to undertake a risk reduction study in support of a planned Main Gate business decision in early 2015.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","207687","2014-09-08T15:08:27.6949056Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90010/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90010/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the merits of integrating MBDA Brimstone 2 air-to-ground precision weapon with the Typhoon aircraft to the UK's defence capabilities.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90011","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p> </p><p>The F-35B development test continues to make steady progress. To date, the F-35 fleet has surpassed 19,500 flight hours. <br><br>UK F-35B Initial Operating Capability remains on track to deliver in 2018.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-08T14:34:34.3821207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90011/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90011/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent progress has been made on development of the F-35 B aircraft.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90012","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-11","<p>Participation in Exercise Red Flag in 2014 was important in maintaining close ties, from strategic to tactical levels, with the USA and Australia, and provided a realistic and testing environment for coalition training for both aircraft and ground based force elements.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-11T15:14:45.2934953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90012/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90012/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90012/answer/previousversion/18966","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the benefits of participation by the Royal Air Force in Exercise Red Flag; and if he will make a statement on the 2014 exercise.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90013","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-11","<p>Participation in Exercise Anatolian Eagle in 2014 at Konya Air base in Turkey afforded UK personnel with the experience of deploying and operating alongside NATO and other potential coalition allies. This includes exposure to the complexities of operating large numbers of aircraft from the same base and in missions of large airborne formations.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-11T15:12:09.3463925Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90013/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90013/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90013/answer/previousversion/18965","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the merits of participation by the Royal Air Force in the Anatolian Eagle 2014 exercise; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90014","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence currently has no plans to use the IRIS-T air-to-air guided missile.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-08T15:17:55.6128598Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90014/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90014/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to use the IRIS-T air-to-air guided missile in the UK's armed forces; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90015","Department for Education","false","2014-09-08","<p>The Cadet Bursary Fund was launched by the Prime Minister on 18 June to help state schools set up, grow and sustain new cadet units. The aim of our Cadet Expansion Programme is to see 100 new state school units established by September 2015. 49 new units have been approved so far.<br> <br> The Cadet Bursary fund will be administered by the Combined Cadet Force Association. The Department for Education is supporting the development of a fundraising strategy to ensure the legacy of the fund.<br> <br> To date, £1,560,000 has been donated or pledged to the fund. This comprises £1 million from Libor funds, £250,000 from Youth United funding and £310,000 from private donations. The fund will open to applications from schools involved in the Cadet Expansion Programme on 15 September, and grant decisions will be announced in early December.<br> <br> We will publish the full details on the application process and detailed guidance for schools shortly.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-09-08T16:48:46.9151623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90015/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90015/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90015/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-01","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent progress she has made on the bursary scheme to set up cadet units in schools.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90016","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>RAF frontline fast jet capability is currently provided by Tornado and Typhoon aircraft supported by Hawk jet training aircraft. <br><br>However, the RAF continues to transition towards a future combined frontline fleet of Lightning II and Typhoon aircraft. Lightning II is a fifth-generation stealth aircraft representing a step-change in the UK’s combat air capability, whilst the Typhoon will provide an enhanced multi-role and Intelligence Surveillance Target Acquisition and Reconnaissance (ISTAR) capability, in addition to its original air defence role.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-08T15:45:27.597788Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90016/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90016/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90016/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make a statement on the current fast jet capability of the Royal Air Force and outline any future developments.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90017","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-13","<p>Between 14 August 1969 and 31 August 2014, 41 soldiers from Scottish regiments died on duty as a result of terrorist activity in Northern Ireland. The last of the 41 deaths occurred in 1993. <br><br>Information on soldiers that were injured is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-13T15:57:04.8016447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90017/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90017/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90017/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90017/answer/previousversion/18961","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) soldiers in Scottish regiments and (b) Scottish soldiers in other regiments were (i) killed and (ii) injured on duty in Northern Ireland during the IRA terrorist campaign.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","207711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90018","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-05","<p> </p><p>The deaths of two soldiers at Abercorn Barracks are a personal tragedy for their families and loved ones, and our thoughts remain with them. As is normal with the death of Armed Forces personnel in the UK, these have been investigated by the local Home Office police force, in this case the Police Service of Northern Ireland. We understand that they have concluded their investigations and passed their conclusions to the Coroner, who is in the process of establishing formal inquests into the soldiers’ deaths. <br><br>An internal service inquiry has been established by the Army to consider the facts and identify any lessons to prevent anything like this happening again. This is a complex inquiry, involving a significant number of witnesses and, while we are seeking to complete it as soon as possible, determining the findings and recommendations will naturally take time. It is important that the inquiry is conducted properly and given the appropriate space to reach its conclusions. The families have been kept informed throughout.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-05T12:20:46.7880164Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90018/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90018/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Military Bases: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on the investigation into the deaths of soldiers at Abercorn barracks in Ballykinler in December 2012 and February 2013.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","207683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90019","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-06","<p>The UK has a number of military assets deployed in support of the US-led humanitarian mission in Iraq, including Tornado GR4s with surveillance capability, a UK Rivet Joint surveillance aircraft, voyager air-to-air refuelling aircraft and C130s.<br><br>We also have a range of other contingent capabilities, some of which are assigned to ongoing or potential operations.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-06T15:34:39.2811513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90019/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90019/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90019/answer/previousversion/18964","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what military capacity is available to support US air strikes in Northern Iraq.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90020","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>The MBDA Brimstone 2 will enhance the multi-role capability of the Typhoon aircraft as it is effective against challenging, high speed and manoeuvring targets over land and sea.<br><br>Work is underway to evaluate the integration of Brimstone 2 with the Typhoon aircraft. On 2 June 2014, BAE Systems was awarded a contract worth in the region of £5 million to undertake a risk reduction study in support of a planned Main Gate business decision in early 2015.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","207659","2014-09-08T15:08:27.7610251Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90020/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90020/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on work to integrate the MBDA Brimstone 2 air-to-ground precision weapon with the Typhoon aircraft; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90021","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-11","<p>As of 3 September 2014, there are two Service personnel deployed to Morocco, two to Algeria, six to Tunisia, and four to Egypt.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-11T15:11:11.6206842Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90021/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90021/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90021/answer/previousversion/18962","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","North Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many service personnel are on active duty in North Africa.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90022","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>The Volunteer Reserve Forces are continuously recruiting and numbers joining are not normally attributed to particular advertising campaigns. In the 12 months ending 31 July 2014, approximately 10 people joined Reserve Units in Warrington.<br><br>Source: Defence Statistics. Numbers have been rounded to the nearest 10.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-09-04T12:55:51.4036542Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90022/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90022/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90022/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Reserve Forces: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people in Warrington have joined the reserve forces as a result of the Government’s recent advertising campaign.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","207618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90023","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>The Sovereign Base Areas Administration (SBAA) and the Government of the Republic of Cyprus published guidelines for the designation of planning zones and the preparation of planning policy for the Sovereign Base Areas of Akrotiri and Dhekelia (SBAs) on 16 July 2014. These draft guidelines are now subject to consultation until the end of October 2014. It is proposed that the SBAA Policy Statement will underpin planning and development in the SBAs, ensuring this is carried out in a controlled manner and that designated special areas of protection and conservation are maintained appropriately.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-04T12:52:56.8470708Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90023/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90023/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90023/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Cyprus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the protected status of every designated nature conservation area in Akrotiri Sovereign Base Area will be maintained following the agreement between the UK and Republic of Cyprus in January 2014 to open the Sovereign Base Area to development.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90024","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>The Sovereign Base Areas Administration (SBAA) and the Government of the Republic of Cyprus are holding a joint consultation process for the designation of planning zones and preparation of planning policy for the Sovereign Base Areas of Akrotiri and Dhekelia (SBAs). Public meetings with representatives of the relevant local communities were held on 16 July 2014, when the formal joint consultation process commenced. The draft proposals for the designation of planning zones and planning policy in the SBAs have been provided to all SBA communities and to various interested Non Government Organisations. The relevant documents can be accessed on the SBAA website, together with accompanying maps providing guidance on current land use and constraints, including existing and proposed special areas of protection and conservation.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-04T12:50:53.310914Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90024/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90024/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90024/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Cyprus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how his Department plans to ensure that any consultation run by the government of the Republic of Cyprus with regard to development of the Akrotiri Sovereign Base Area will include consultation with civil society.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90025","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p>Recruitment for the Joint Cyber Unit (Reserve) began in October 2013. The Cyber Reserve will provide support to the Joint Cyber Unit (Corsham), the Joint Cyber Unit (Cheltenham), and tri-service Information Assurance units. Interest in joining the Cyber Reserve has been extremely positive, both in terms of the quality and quantity of applications received. A number of Cyber Reservist applicants have been selected and are now going through single Service recruiting processes, with many more being invited to interview. The first Cyber Reserve Induction Courses have taken place and these individuals will now move onto specific workplace induction and training. The next two years will see the Cyber Reserve fully operational.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-09-04T12:54:34.3833251Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90025/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90025/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90025/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the status is of the Cyber Reserve.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","207634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90026","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-06","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) has robust measures in place to prepare our Service personnel for civilian life as well as addressing any accommodation, employment, welfare, health and domestic needs and concerns. While in Service, our personnel can receive skills, qualifications and experience accredited to nationally recognised standards to ease the transition back into the civilian workplace. <br><br>The MOD and the Department for Education have worked closely together on the Troops for Teachers Programme. This is a coherent programme that Service leavers can use to access teaching opportunities to increase the number of high-quality Service leavers joining the teaching profession. The MOD and the Career Transition Partnership (CTP) (the MOD’s employment support partner for personnel leaving the Armed Forces) promote the programme through various channels including CTP organised career events for Service personnel; through internal Defence media (such as the Defence Intranet); and through resettlement briefings which take place at CTP centres across the UK. The CTP continues to be successful. Of those personnel who access the CTP, 85% are in employment within six months of them leaving the Armed Forces.<br><br>The new two-year, school-based Troops to Teachers programme started in January 2014 and has been designed and developed together with a group of outstanding schools and initial teacher training providers and with the CTP. It uses a rigorous assessment, selection and recruitment process to identify those Service leavers with the potential to become outstanding teachers. This process also recognises the professional skills Service leavers already have and provides training to make best use of and further develop them in schools. Good progress was made in recruiting 41 eligible Service leavers for the first cohort of this scheme. Trainees in the first cohort are in their second term of school-based training and feedback from host schools has been positive.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-06T15:35:42.4125885Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90026/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90026/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90026/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90026/answer/previousversion/18973","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Teachers: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to encourage veterans to consider teaching as a post-service career option.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","207697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90027","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>Home-Start has received payments totalling £40,335 from the Armed Forces Community Covenant Grant Scheme for two projects in the UK. No funding has been awarded to the charity for any projects in Germany, Cyprus or elsewhere abroad.</p><p> </p><p>The Community Covenant Grant Scheme (CCGS) is a fund of £30 million designed to support projects at the local level that strengthen ties between members of the Armed Forces community and the wider community.</p><p> </p><p>An application for funding can be submitted by any part of the community (e.g. volunteer groups, charities and public bodies such as schools) firstly through the Community Covenant partnership and if endorsed at that level, to the regional panels up and down the country. Although this is the last year of the CCGS, from 2015 the Armed Forces Covenant fund will launch with £10 million per year made available to fund projects supporting the Armed Forces.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T16:19:21.872144Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90027/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90027/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90027/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90027/answer/previousversion/18971","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Home Start","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much funding his Department provides to support the charity Homestart in (a) Germany, (b) Cyprus, (c) elsewhere abroad and (d) the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","207738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90028","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>The UK Armed Forces Quarterly Personnel report, which is published by Defence Statistics, shows Reserve trained and untrained strength figures, as well as movements into the Future Reserves 2020 population. It is available on the www.gov.uk website at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-armed-forces-quarterly-personnel-report-2014</p><p> </p><p>The trained strength of the Future Reserves 2020 population as at 1 April 2014 exceeded the target figures set out in the Written Ministerial Statement and paper that the former Defence Secretary, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) placed in the Library of the House on 19 December 2013, (Official Report, column 124WS), as shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>1 April 2014</strong></p><p><strong>Target</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1 April 2014 Actual</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>21,780</p></td><td><p>22,480</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Maritime Reserve</strong></p></td><td><p>1,780</p></td><td><p>1,870</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Army Reserve</strong></p></td><td><p>18,800</p></td><td><p>19,400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>RAuxiliaryAF</strong></p></td><td><p>1,200</p></td><td><p>1,220</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We are committed to achieving our target of 35,000 trained Reserves by the end of 2018-19.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-09-08T15:53:26.9142388Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90028/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90028/answer","20131219 - Hansard Extract Future Reserves 2020.doc","20131219 - Hansard Extract Future Reserves 2020.doc","Hansard extract - Future Reserves 2020","Hansard extract - Future Reserves 2020","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90028/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people were recruited to the Reserve forces in the last 12 months; how this figure compares to his Department's target figures; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","207735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90029","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p><strong>The Rt Hon Mark Francois: </strong></p><p> </p><p>The number of sorties in which RAF crews have utilised a USAF Reaper to undertake a UK Sortie in Afghanistan for each year between 2008 and 2014 is given in the following table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of United Kingdom Sorties utilising a USAF Air Vehicle</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>64</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>56</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-January to August Inclusive</p></td><td><p>192</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>For the majority of occasions this was due to short term unserviceability or routine scheduled servicing of a UK Reaper. The increased usage in 2012 was due to an increase in ISAF tasking, coinciding with a period of reduced UK airframe availability. This resulted in reduced resilience to cover short-term unserviceabilities from within the UK Reaper force. The increased usage in 2014 was due to further increased ISAF tasking utilising the crews from the UK Additional Reaper Capability. The additional UK aircrews and ISAF requirement to start the new task lines were in place prior to the additional UK airframes being prepared for operations in theatre. Consequently, while the new UK airframes were temporarily unavailable for tasking, the additional ISAF task lines with UK crews were flown utilising USAF aircraft.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T17:00:19.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90029/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90029/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90029/answer/previousversion/18968","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions UK forces have used a US Air Force Reaper Remotely Piloted Air System in Afghanistan in each year; and whether each such use was due to serviceability issues with RAF Reaper Remotely Piloted Air Systems.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","207734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90030","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>UK forces were deployed to Northern Iraq in 1991 in support of Operation Safe Haven. These forces included:<br><br>Twelve Chinook helicopters based at Diyarbakir Air Base in Turkey and <br>at its peak, approximately, 4,000 UK service personnel in Turkey and Northern Iraq.<br><br>3 Commando Brigade Royal Marines was deployed. In addition to helicopter support, three RAF C-130 aircraft were also deployed. The last Coalition land forces related to this operation withdrew from Northern Iraq on 16 July 1991.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T16:20:19.3684729Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90030/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90030/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90030/answer/previousversion/18969","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) Chinook helicopters, (b) personnel and (c) other assets were involved in Operation Safe Haven; and when that operation finished.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","207732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90031","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>None.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-08T15:56:54.0130154Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90031/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90031/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","C17 Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what weight of goods has been air-dropped by C-17 aircraft during (a) exercises and (b) operations in each location since those aircraft entered service.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","207733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90032","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no plans to charge market rates for Service Personnel accommodation or to introduce geographical variations. Charges will continue to be subject to the recommendations of the Armed Forces Pay Review Body (AFPRB). The AFPRB’s approach is to recommend charges that are linked to the costs faced by civilians, but with a significant subsidy to recognise the drawbacks of living in Service accommodation. <br><br>Under this approach, personnel in Service accommodation will continue to pay a significantly smaller percentage of their earnings on accommodation charges than would be likely in the private sector. Any claims for benefits are a private matter for the individual and therefore the Department does not hold any data.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","207592 ; 207593 ; 207594","2014-09-08T14:04:17.7300589Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90032/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/90032/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-01","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make a statement about his plans to increase married quarters rents to market levels.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","Mr James Gray","207595"
